Barcelona came from beheind to beat
Sevilla 2-1 as  Lionel Messi  scored in his record-extending 15th
consecutive game in Spanish soccerâ€™s La Liga.  Alberto Botia gave Sevilla the lead just before halftime at
the Nou Camp stadium in Barcelona.  David Villa  tied the game in
